ðŸ“¦ Containerized Recommendation Service (Python)
This microservice, written in python, was containerized using a docker file as python applications needs no build used single stage

ðŸ”¨ Build Stage
* Pulled the official python:slim-bookworm base image from Docker Hub registry.
* Set the WORKDIR to /usr/src/app for structured and consistent builds in container.
* Copied the source code from current directory into the container workdirectory
* Installed python libraries specified in requirements.txt file
* Defined python program in Entrypoint to run 

# Dockerfile

FROM python:3.12-slim-bookworm AS base
WORKDIR /usr/src/app
COPY requirements.txt ./

RUN pip install --upgrade pip
RUN pip install -r requirements.txt

COPY . .

ENTRYPOINT [ "python", "recommendation_server.py"]
                                               
#After creating the docker file build the docker image and run the image 
#added ubuntu user to the docker group so no need root previlage
docker build -t "image name" (any tag you want to put for the image)
docker run "imagename"
